body:
@lcamargof Try to reset the account because when you spawn a new node the account's nonce value stays as it was on the previous node. On a new node it has to start from 0 again.

Probably the gas estimation problem is due to this nonce mismatch. (any many other problems that may look weird, strange errors etc.)

`MetaMask: "Settings-> Advanced -> Reset Account"`

In case anyone is in desperate need to get past this, I did a very dirty patch on the file
`node_modules/hardhat/internal/hardhat-network/provider/modules/eth.js`
in the function `_feeHistoryAction` so the function starts with:
```
    async _feeHistoryAction(blockCount, newestBlock, rewardPercentiles) {
        var _a;
        if (!this._node.isEip1559Active()) {
            throw new errors_1.InvalidInputError(`eth_feeHistory is disabled. It only works with the London hardfork or a later one.`);
        }
        return {
            oldestBlock: '0xd67c1e',
            baseFeePerGas: [ '0x53f71a32', '0x497836ec' ],
            gasUsedRatio: [ 0 ],
            reward: [ [ '0x0', '0x0' ] ]
        }
```
The values are arbitrary (copied from a successful invocation of the function) and I didnt care much about them (yet). Replace them as you see fit.

If you use patch-package you can also put the patch file (rename to remove .txt extension) in the /patches folder : [hardhat+2.8.4.patch.txt](https://github.com/NomicFoundation/hardhat/files/8101568/hardhat%2B2.8.4.patch.txt)
